{"id":22932,"title":"The management of acute appendicitis.","abstract":"Appendicitis is the most common general surgical condition and peaks in incidence at the age of those serving in the military. Diagnosis can be extremely difficult with very vague signs and symptoms. This review aims to highlight management considerations that should be taken into account when faced with appendicitis in a military setting, including in the pre-hospital and pre-shore environment. Current controversies surrounding appendicitis management, and the effect these might have on the management of the military patient, are debated.","date":"2014-02-11","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24511791","annotations":[{"name":"Surgery","weight":0.733837,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surgery"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.669249,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Diagnosis","weight":0.534623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diagnosis"},{"name":"Symptom","weight":0.458165,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Symptom"},{"name":"Emergency medical services","weight":0.427452,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emergency_medical_services"},{"name":"Acute (medicine)","weight":0.338178,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acute_(medicine)"},{"name":"Incidence (epidemiology)","weight":0.322139,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Incidence_(epidemiology)"},{"name":"General surgery","weight":0.243685,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General_surgery"},{"name":"Appendicitis","weight":0.144978,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Appendicitis"},{"name":"Military","weight":0.0805305,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Military"},{"name":"Medical sign","weight":0.0422074,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medical_sign"},{"name":"General officer","weight":0.030